      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think the only thing that was broken was that `rdb stream` unconditionally killed its payload (e.g. result_adapter) on getting an interrupt.",
      "revId": "c51e6a6d10b208336418ea453d4bf09eadb7eec0",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "46f5b385_83ae110f",
        "filename": "resultdb/cli/cmd_stream.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 62,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-05-27T11:19:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s not always true that rdb-stream runs by a swarming task. Also, the GracePeriodSecs applies to the swarming raw_cmd, and rdb-stream may not be the beginning command in raw_cmd\n(i.e., the parent process of rdb-stream may also need a second to clean up for itself)\n\nIt\u0027s the parent process\u0027 responsibility to set the deadlines in luci-ctx to advise the child process for the appropriate deadline. If deadline is not set in the luci-ctx, rdb-stream should not enforce a deadline to its child process, either.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 58,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 62,
        "endChar": 17
      },
      "revId": "c51e6a6d10b208336418ea453d4bf09eadb7eec0",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
